			<CASNumber>CID 24586</CASNumber>
			<common:generalComment xml:lang="en">Nickel Sulfate is a crystalline inorganic compound that is yellow, green or blue coloured and produces toxic gasses upon heating. It is used in electroplating and as a chemical intermediate to produce other types of nickel compounds. It is a by-product of copper refining and it naturally occurs as a rare mineral which is retgersite. It is a highly soluble salt and depending on its state, it can be either blue, green, or yellow colored. It is commonly used in the production of various nickel-based compounds and also acts as a common source for Ni2+ ions used in electroplating.</common:generalComment>
			<common:generalComment xml:lang="zh">硫酸镍是一种结晶性无机化合物，呈黄色、绿色或蓝色，加热时会产生有毒气体。它用于电镀，也是生产其他类型镍化合物的化学中间体。它是铜精炼的副产品，天然存在于一种稀有矿物中，即雷公石。它是一种高溶解性盐，根据其状态，可以呈现蓝色、绿色或黄色。它通常用于生产各种镍基化合物，也是电镀中使用的 Ni2+ 离子的常见来源。</common:generalComment>
